oakcurric:unit-3400
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Food and healthy communities"@en ;
  curric:slug "food-and-healthy-communities" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit the food and dietary needs of different groups are examined. Dishes
  and meals are planned, based on their specific needs and healthy eating guidelines. Pupils
  make an oven baked veggie korma to celebrate with their school community."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Eating a healthy, varied diet is an important part of maintaining good
  health and reducing ill-health in our communities. Using learning from previous units,
  through the threads of Healthy eating and nutrition, Consumer awareness, and Food culture,
  dishes and meals can be planned and prepared to meet needs as they change throughout life.
  These threads continue to be developed in Year 7, examining additional factors affecting food
  choice and food customs.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3400-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3400-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3400-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3400-4 ;
  curric:id "3400"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.834981Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-culture ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety ,
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation .

oakcurric:unit-3387
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Food origins: from farm to fork"@en ;
  curric:slug "food-origins-from-farm-to-fork" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit investigates food grown, reared and caught in the UK and around the
  globe. Pupils name and locate food origins, expanding their experiences of food and
  cuisines. They make apple flapjacks, identifying ingredients from the UK."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """While much of our food is from the UK, a significant proportion is sourced
  globally. Knowing its origin allows us to make decisions. This builds on from the Food
  origins and provenance thread in Year 2, food being grown, reared and caught. In Year 4, more
  sustainable eating is introduced via the Sustainability thread, with learning around food
  seasonality, local foods, and reducing food waste.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3387-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3387-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3387-3 ;
  curric:id "3387"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.865162Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-culture ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3390
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "The Eatwell Guide: for me and you"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-eatwell-guide-for-me-and-you" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils map and plan meals inline with the Eatwell Guide food groups,
  suggesting improvements for the future. Pupils make a frittata, highlighting the food
  group included, as well as possible additions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Our diets, the food and drink consumed over time, should follow the food
  groups and proportions as depicted in the Eatwell Guide. Being able to plan against these
  principles helps to establish healthier eating patterns, as well as address less healthy
  patterns. This builds on previous learning through the Healthy eating and nutrition thread,
  such as knowing the food groups, and putting advice into practice. Energy and nutrients
  provided by the food groups, and their role, are examined in Year 5.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3390-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3390-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3390-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3390-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3390-5 ;
  curric:id "3390"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.867158Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3393
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Creative cooking"@en ;
  curric:slug "creative-cooking" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit focuses on being creative with food, looking at how recipes can be
  adapted. Changing ingredients, forming different shapes and great presentation are
  covered. Food skills are further secured, with attention to health and safety."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Being able to adapt recipes for different needs, food availability, added
  interest and occasion, broadens recipe repertoire, food skills and techniques. This is
  possible through food understanding and handling, and cultural context learning. Building on
  from Food preparation and cooking, and Food hygiene and safety learning in Year 4, accurate
  measuring and key food skills are secured through practice. Greater precision and accuracy
  using a range of food skills is emphasised in Year 6, developing self-confidence and more
  independent working.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3393-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3393-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3393-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3393-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3393-5 ;
  curric:id "3393"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.898353Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3388
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Global food and dishes"@en ;
  curric:slug "global-food-and-dishes" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils are introduced to a range of food and dishes, some familiar
  and some unfamiliar. They explore different ingredients, equipment and utensils used
  globally, and make an 'international' salad."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Through the study of global cuisine, an appreciation for the wide variety
  of ingredients, equipment, cooking techniques and eating styles is established. This expands
  traditional and cultural factors highlighted in Year 2 around bread, developing the Consumer
  awareness and Food culture threads. The planning and composition of different meals and
  snacks are developed in Year 4, focusing on real choices made everyday, whether eating in or
  outside the home.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3388-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3388-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3388-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3388-4 ;
  curric:id "3388"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.012547Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-culture ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3399
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Safe and edible food"@en ;
  curric:slug "safe-and-edible-food" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils explore different ways to store, prepare and cook food so that it is safe
  to eat. They examine food labels for safety and quality assurance marks, and make Cornish
  pasties to apply their food safety and food origins learning."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Good food safety and hygiene is essential to make sure that the food we
  buy, store, cook, and eat is safe. It helps prevent food poisoning. Food labels help us to
  store and cook food to ensure safety, along with hygienic practices. This builds on work
  around food hygiene learning in Year 5, following procedures to ensure good food safety. The
  Food hygiene and safety, and The science of food threads are further developed and embedded
  in Year 7, highlighting ways in which the risk of food poisoning can be minimised.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3399-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3399-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3399-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3399-4 ;
  curric:id "3399"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.023535Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3389
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Cooking for life"@en ;
  curric:slug "cooking-for-life" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit focuses on weighing and measuring, making three dishes to refine food
  skills. Historical context and science through food is explored during cooking activity."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Accurate weighing and measuring is essential, so that recipes can be
  replicated, as well as cook safely and thoroughly. Historical context highlights how our food
  is woven in our society, and changes over decades, and The science of food thread explores
  how and why ingredients change when cooked. The use of numeracy builds on counting
  ingredients and using spoons as a measure in earlier cooking units. In Year 5, the thread of
  Food preparation and cooking focuses on being creative and how recipes can be modified for
  different people and occasions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3389-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3389-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3389-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3389-4 ;
  curric:id "3389"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.218452Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-culture ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3386
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Food and drink choices"@en ;
  curric:slug "food-and-drink-choices" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils explore the factors that determine what people eat and drink.
  They investigate and plan food for different occasions and celebrations, and make tuna
  canapés for a party."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """The food and drink we choose depends on a wide range of factors, and some
  of these change through life. By studying these factors, as well as special occasions,
  pupils' ability to plan and justify food choices for others and contexts improves. This unit
  builds on Eatwell Guide messaging from Year 2, and in the future units the thread of Healthy
  eating and nutrition is put into practice to plan meals and snacks for themselves and others.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3386-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3386-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3386-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3386-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3386-5 ;
  curric:id "3386"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.329398Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
