    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-culture ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3395
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Food production"@en ;
  curric:slug "food-production" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit goes through different ways in which our food is produced and processed,
  using a range of examples. The reasons why and how our food is processed is highlighted.
  Pupils identify the origin of ingredients through cooking a baked dish."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Food production and processing supports the food needs of countries
  throughout the world, whether domestically or on a larger scale. Knowing how food is
  produced, and how and why food is processed, enables us to make informed choices about the
  food we buy, prepare, cook and eat. This builds on previous unit's learning around Food
  origins and provenance, Consumer awareness, and Sustainability. Pupils progress this learning
  through examining the importance of how and why food is stored, prepared and cooked for
  safety in Year 6.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3395-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3395-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3395-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3395-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3395-5 ;
  curric:id "3395"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.641092Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-sustainability-and-climate-change ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3392
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Meal occasions and smart snacks"@en ;
  curric:slug "meal-occasions-and-smart-snacks" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils investigate and make smart snack swaps, as well as explore how
  the food and drink we consume at home can differ to that eaten outside the home. Pupils
  plan and make breakfast muffins for their school friends."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """While much of what we consume is through meals, many people consume
  snacks. The choice of snack is important and should contribute to a healthy, varied diet
  overall. Poor snack choices can contribute to our overall daily energy (calorie) intake.
  Building on previous Healthy eating and nutrition learning in Years 3 and 4, snack swaps, and
  food eaten in and out of the home, can be mapped to ensure healthier eating patterns. The
  threads of Consumer awareness, such as food choice, and Food culture, are expanded in Year 5,
  addressing customs, traditions, and special occasions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3392-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3392-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3392-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3392-4 ;
  curric:id "3392"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.682161Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3385
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Cooking around the world"@en ;
  curric:slug "cooking-around-the-world" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops pupils' food skills through the context of food from around the
  world. Pupils learn about the structure of a recipe, how to portion foods evenly and, with
  supervision, use heat in cooking."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Through an international context, pupils' food skills progress via
  accurate food portioning (cutting and measuring), to achieve even cooking. Food skills are
  reinforced from cooking experiences in Year 2, with additional skills being introduced. The
  use of heat expands dish repertoire, allowing for more complex recipes to be made. The
  threads of Food preparation and cooking, and Food hygiene and safety, are further developed
  and refined in Year 3.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3385-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3385-2 ,
