oakcurric:unit-3397
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Cooking showcase"@en ;
  curric:slug "cooking-showcase" ;
  rdfs:comment """Through three recipes, pupils showcase accurate and precise food skills through
  dicing, weighing and measuring, and portioning, as well as presentation techniques. Pupils
  will be more confident and show greater independence in their cooking."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Becoming more secure and confident in preparing and cooking food enables
  us to work more independently, competently and accurately. These learning experiences enable
  further exploration of recipes and cuisines. This builds on Year 5, adapting recipes for
  different needs and broadening recipe repertoire, bringing together multiple threads,
  including Food preparation and cooking, and Food hygiene and safety. This sets the scene for
  transitioning to Year 7, where food skills and knowledge will be applied to working in a
  different environment, using an extended range of ingredients and equipment.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3397-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3397-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3397-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3397-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3397-5 ;
  curric:id "3397"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.934570Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3391
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Seasonal food and ingredients"@en ;
  curric:slug "seasonal-food-and-ingredients" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores the seasons in the UK and the seasonal fruit and vegetables
  available. Pupils examine the benefits of using local food and list ways to reduce food
  waste. Pupils create and make a salad using seasonal produce."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Eating more seasonal fruit and vegetables and locally produced food, as
  well as reducing food waste, helps to achieve a more healthy and sustainable diet. Having
  pragmatic advice and strategies enables us to make better decisions about the foods we use
  and consume. Focus on the Consumer awareness, Food origins and provenance, and Sustainability
  threads develop learning making informed food decisions. These threads progress further in
  Year 5, where food production and processing at different scales are examined.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3391-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3391-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3391-3 ;
  curric:id "3391"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.061022Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-sustainability-and-climate-change ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3398
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Healthy eating in action"@en ;
  curric:slug "healthy-eating-in-action" ;
  rdfs:comment """In the unit pupils apply key healthy eating messages to their own and others'
  diets. They examine and use food labels to make healthier choices, and calculate the
  energy and nutrients provided by a recipe that they make."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Making informed food and drink choices, in meaningful and practical ways,
  is vital for healthier lives. Building on investigating energy and nutrients, and their food
  sources and functions for health in Year 5, strategies can be used to make informed choices
  for ourselves and others through reading food labels, and applying healthy eating and
  nutrition advice. In Year 7 these strategies are developed, using the Eatwell Guide to
  justify food and drink choices for different people and occasions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3398-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3398-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3398-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3398-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3398-5 ;
  curric:id "3398"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.205447Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3394
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Food for energy and nutrients"@en ;
  curric:slug "food-for-energy-and-nutrients" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils investigate food and drinks providing energy and nutrients for
  our health. They explore some of the functions of nutrients, as well as food sources. Main
  nutrients are linked to the Eatwell Guide food groups."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Food and drinks provide the energy and nutrients required by the body to
  grow, be active and maintain health. Being able to describe different nutrients, and their
  sources and function, gives an appreciation for the need and importance of a varied and
  balanced diet for good nutrition. This learning extends the Healthy eating and nutrition
  thread from Year 4, showing how the Eatwell Guide conveys nutrition messaging via food
  groups. In Year 6, pupils use and apply Healthy eating and nutrition messages to their own
  and others' diets.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3394-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3394-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3394-3 ;
  curric:id "3394"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.343920Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

